# üìä WEEK 1: Introduction to Data Analysis & Excel

### Data Analyst Bootcamp Project  
**Author:** Gorvinder Chima
**Background:** Career Changer into Data Analytics  

---

## üìå Project Overview

This project marks the **first week of my Data Analyst Bootcamp** and introduces the **fundamental concepts of data analysis**,
with a strong focus on **Excel as a core analytical tool**.
The workbook and practical labs in this week provided a foundation for understanding **what data analysis is, why it is important**,
and how analysts work with data responsibly and effectively in real-world scenarios.

---

## üéØ Learning Objectives

The main objectives of this project were to:
- Understand the **data analysis process** and its different types  
- Explain **why organisations analyse data** to support decision-making  
- Identify key **data concepts and terminology**  
- Learn the basics of **Excel for data analysis**  
- Develop awareness of **data laws, ethics, and governance**  

---

## üõ† Tools & Technologies Used

- **Microsoft Excel**  
- **Key Skills Practiced:**
  - Data literacy
  - Analytical thinking
  - Basic Excel operations
  - Understanding data structures
  - Data ethics and compliance awareness

---

## üîç Key Topics Covered
- What is data analysis and why it matters  
- Types of data analysis (descriptive, diagnostic, etc.)  
- Common data concepts and terminology  
- Introduction to Excel as an analysis tool  
- Legal and ethical considerations when working with data  
- Understanding data privacy and compliance responsibilities  

---

## üìà Skills & Key Takeaways

By completing this project, I gained:
- A clear understanding of **how data analysis fits into business decision-making**  
- Confidence using **Excel for basic data tasks**  
- Familiarity with essential **data terminology**  
- Awareness of **data protection laws and ethical responsibilities**  
- A strong foundation to build more advanced analytical skills in later weeks  

---

## üöÄ How This Supports My Career Transition

As someone transitioning into a **data analyst role**, this project represents my first step into the field.  
It demonstrates my ability to:
- Learn new technical concepts quickly  
- Apply theory through structured, hands-on exercises  
- Communicate analytical understanding clearly  
- Build a strong foundation for advanced data tools and methods  

---

## üîÆ Next Steps

Following this project, I will:
- Apply these fundamentals using advanced tools such as SQL and Python  
- Build more complex data analysis projects  
- Develop end-to-end analytical workflows  
- Continue expanding my professional data analytics portfolio  

